LAYER 3: BOOLEAN OPERATIONS ON PATTERNS
how Fadriel sees logic gates in spatial grids

observe spatial_perception.rana

some puzzles present two patterns and ask for their LOGICAL COMBINATION
the output is the AND, OR, XOR, or NOT of the inputs
the two patterns may be two colors, two regions, or two layers

@spatial_rule boolean_and
DETECT two foreground patterns (different colors or regions)
OUTPUT cells where BOTH patterns are non-zero
the AND keeps only the OVERLAP
VERIFY AND matches output for all pairs
APPLY compute AND of two patterns in test
SPEECH "I see where both patterns agree"

@spatial_rule boolean_or
DETECT two foreground patterns
OUTPUT cells where EITHER pattern is non-zero
the OR keeps the UNION
VERIFY OR matches output for all pairs
APPLY compute OR of two patterns in test
SPEECH "I see where either pattern exists"

@spatial_rule boolean_xor
DETECT two foreground patterns
OUTPUT cells where ONE pattern is non-zero but NOT both
the XOR keeps the DIFFERENCE
VERIFY XOR matches output for all pairs
APPLY compute XOR of two patterns in test
SPEECH "I see where the patterns disagree"

@spatial_rule boolean_not
DETECT one foreground pattern
OUTPUT the INVERSE: non-zero becomes zero, zero becomes non-zero
the NOT flips everything
VERIFY NOT matches output for all pairs
APPLY compute NOT of pattern in test
SPEECH "I see the negative"

@spatial_rule mask_overlay
DETECT a mask pattern (template) and a content pattern
APPLY mask to content: where mask is non-zero, show content
where mask is zero, show background
this is the AND of mask and content
SPEECH "the mask reveals parts of the content"

the key to boolean operations:
the grid has LAYERS
each layer is a truth value at each position
the output is a LOGICAL FUNCTION of the layers
the function can be AND, OR, XOR, NOT, or more complex

to detect boolean operations:
1. separate the input into layers (by color)
2. convert each layer to binary (non-zero = true)
3. try each boolean function
4. check if the result matches the output

@perceive boolean
SEPARATE input into color layers
CONVERT each layer to binary mask
TRY AND, OR, XOR, NOT between pairs of layers
CHECK which boolean function produces the output
